TITLE: Configuring Button Story Metadata in Svelte (Standard CSF) with JavaScript
DESCRIPTION: Defines the metadata for Button component stories in a Svelte project using standard Component Story Format (CSF) in a JavaScript file. It imports the `Button.svelte` component and exports a default object specifying the component, `argTypes` for controls (like a color picker for `backgroundColor`), and default `args` (setting `primary` to true for all stories).
SOURCE: https://github.com/storybookjs/storybook/blob/next/docs/_snippets/button-story-component-args-primary.md#2025-04-22_snippet_8

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
```js filename="Button.stories.js" renderer="svelte" language="js" tabTitle="CSF"
import Button from './Button.svelte';

export default {
  component: Button,
  //üëá Creates specific argTypes
  argTypes: {
    backgroundColor: { control: 'color' },
  },
  args: {
    //üëá Now all Button stories will be primary.
    primary: true,
  },
};
