TITLE: Defining and Rendering Storybook Stories for a React Component - JavaScript
DESCRIPTION: This snippet demonstrates how to configure a Storybook story for a React component in JavaScript, including setting up argTypes for prop controls and using a custom render function to inject calculated props. It requires Storybook for React, a compatible React environment, and expects functional React components and standard JSX. Arguments are used to parametrize the story and control the rendered component's state.
