TITLE: Defining and Decorating React Storybook Component - JavaScript
DESCRIPTION: This snippet defines a Storybook story for MyComponent in React using JavaScript. It applies a decorator to highlight specified elements using Storybook's Preview API. Dependencies include 'storybook/preview-api' and 'storybook/highlight'.
SOURCE: https://github.com/storybookjs/storybook/blob/next/docs/_snippets/component-story-highlight-addon.md#2025-04-22_snippet_1

LANGUAGE: js
CODE:
```
import { useChannel } from 'storybook/preview-api';
import { HIGHLIGHT } from 'storybook/highlight';

import { MyComponent } from './MyComponent';

export default {
  component: MyComponent,
};

export const Highlighted = {
  decorators: [
    (storyFn) => {
      const emit = useChannel({});
      emit(HIGHLIGHT, {
        elements: ['h2', 'a', '.storybook-button'],
      });
      return storyFn();
    },
  ],
};
```

