TITLE: Defining Vue Storybook Button Stories with Render Function (JavaScript)
DESCRIPTION: Defines stories for a Button Vue component in Storybook JavaScript with a custom render function. The render returns a setup-driven template, binding all args to the Vue Button component for reactivity. Useful for advanced or dynamic story rendering in Storybook Vue setups. Requires Vue, Button component, Storybook/vue3.
SOURCE: https://github.com/storybookjs/storybook/blob/next/docs/_snippets/button-story-with-args.md#2025-04-22_snippet_14

LANGUAGE: js
CODE:
```
import Button from './Button.vue';

export default {
  component: Button,
};

/*
 *üëá Render functions are a framework specific feature to allow you control on how the component renders.
 * See https://storybook.js.org/docs/api/csf
 * to learn how to use render functions.
 */
export const Primary = {
  render: (args) => ({
    components: { Button },
    setup() {
      return { args };
    },
    template: '<Button v-bind="args" />',
  }),
  args: {
    primary: true,
    label: 'Button',
  },
};
```

